      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs (blood viscosity, power-law coefficients, inlet velocity profile) characterized with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation results linked to a formal sensitivity analysis identifying dominant drivers.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ completed with 1000 Latin hypercube samples propagating viscosity and power-law coefficient uncertainty. Input distributions assigned from literature. However, no sensitivity analysis artifact has been produced or linked; the relative contribution of each uncertain input to hemolysis index variance remains uncharacterized. We plan to extend with sensitivity analysis in a future revision. Factor not assessed at the required level."
